rComments: His slides are amazing!!!! Everything on the test and exam was based on it! I only read his slides and managed to get high 80s on the exam! However, his practicals were pretty difficult if you don't put enough effort into it (like me). Overall, the prof was great! My Biggest tip is to focus on the slide and put effort into the assignment!

I'm not a science student and took this class to fill out the science distribution needed to graduate. I have zero background knowledge on science and this class is not for me. There is 2 tests and 5 practicals where they all require memorizing 6 powerpoints, contained 50+ slides on each. You must be devoted to memorizing and going to office hours.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lecture heavy', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Dr. Porter was a really wonderful professor. My friend and I are not science students, but we did well in his class because he taught so well and made the material so interesting. I do not recommend skipping class since he hints at the exam and tests in lectures and gets most of the content from them. Also, his voice is very calming and soothing.

Good lecturer, very approachable, and patient with questions. Expectations for assignments are clear and the field work is fun. The textbook is useful but you don't absolutely have to have it. Go to class! He gives lots of exam hints. Do the work and you will be rewarded.

Maybe it was the room he had to teach in (which was quite dim and small), his lecture material was awesome but he always ended up making me want to sleep. And the way he speaks, he always makes "um" or "ugh" sounds during his lectures, which, gosh, just makes people lose track of what he was talking about unfortunately. Regardless, he's very sweet.

He is a really helpful professor and very friendly. The course itself is very interesting and most content are in the lecture which he mainly goes through during class, no extra content  is needed and the use of the textbook is very little to none. There is a lot of field work and reports which were all enjoyable!! Great prof!!

He is one of the greatest and sweetest Profs at UTM! Very kind, very helpful, and very approachable! His tests are very easy, but they sometimes contain trivia questions for which you have to do the readings. Fair grader. Provides excellent lecture slides. Very friendly. Delivers material clearly. I had an excellent experience in this course!!
